{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the researchers noted that existing conceptual models and labeling schemas were unsuitable for law enforcement purposes.",
    "To address this problem, they manually labeled over 4000 unique Tor pages.",
    "There are other examples where researcher resorts to annual labeling for dark web content classification [50,51].There are also challenges associated with the lack of standardization in the content available on the dark web.",
    "As a decentralized network, dark web content is not regulated by any governing body.",
    "Therefore, dark web monitoring tools should be flexible enough to handle various content types and formats."
  ]
}